                My friends started calling me <span style="color: #f15d65">The Nomad</span> because I would travel all over Ghana from <strong>makerspace</strong> to <strong>makerspace</strong> just to talk to developers to gather ideas and
                perspectives. I figured the Tech Atmosphere in Ghana is greatly advancing. And at the heart of this advancement is the <span style="color: #0087cc">magical</span>, <span style="color:#ffaa00;">intimate revelations</span> of the <span
                    style="color: #048a7c">youth</span>. But this driving force is greatly sabotaged by <b>Self Doubt</b>, <b>Little Support</b>, <b>Fewer Known Mentors</b>, and the <b>Lack of an Active Tech Community</b>.
            </p>
            <p class="lead" style="color: #353F49;">
